            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I may be interested in joining this effort, but I guess there are open questions still.\n\nI see the rationale in defining Nvim internal terminal representation data structure (alongside with `src/nvim/tui/tui.c` usage), which could be mapped directly at the point of invoking `update_terminfo.sh` (as suggested by @justinmk ). \nCould be a valid 1st stage subtask of the overall solution?\n\n(Regarding `libtickit`: May worth to note that  [has an optional dependency on](https://github.com/leonerd/libtickit/blob/master/Makefile#L22-L30) on unilibium.)\n\nAny opinions? Suggestions for further steps? \n(Having evaluated the proposed options I couldn't form a strong opinion, but I'm not an expert on the area :-) )",
